  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison&apos;s baby Elizabeth Pease Garrison died at 1 o&apos;clock this morning. He describes her illness, frailty, and death. For a month, Garrison&apos;s house has been like a hospital, violently sick with influenza. William L. Garrison describes his symptoms and ailments. Garrison meditates on life in a spiritual body: &quot;By and by we shall all throw off this robe of mortality, and thus be delivered from &apos;the ills that flesh is heir to.&apos; To exist in a spiritual body, subject to no sickness or decay, is an animating thought, and may well reconcile us to a temporary sojourn here, while it makes the act of earthly dissolution far from being an event to be deplored.&quot; Henry C. Wright returned last night and is staying with William L. Garrison.</subfield>
